    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="674"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.111/154.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs says that no further extension can be granted to
                    Daniel John, as he has had two extensions of delay, and he will have to act in
                    accordance with his agreement to liquidate his business in the time allowed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
